This article is about an executive order signed by President Barack Obama in June 2015. The order establishes the Advisory Board on Toxic Substances and Worker Health within the Department of Labor. The board is responsible for advising the Secretary of Labor on various issues related to worker health, including site exposure matrices, medical guidance for claims examiners, evidentiary requirements for claims related to lung disease, and the work of industrial hygienists and physicians. The board consists of no more than 15 members appointed by the Secretary of Labor in consultation with organizations with expertise in worker health issues. The board will receive funding and administrative support from the Department of Labor and will terminate after 5 years. The executive order does not affect the authority of other agencies or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.